<subSubSection id="1A90241263BC10710F13A6B2CCD1ECFA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E6D3582CA77D914E49451158AE270DA5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4803345CE4EFE7CDD938EADBFB554890" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9F5C5EE78B0AE4BF8FD113104EB3B438" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aurifolia">
<emphasis id="29D776B707499AA639AB1DF4688E4032" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea aurifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but leaves oblong, rather than lanceolate, narrower (&lt;7 mm wide) and much more thinly hairy, outer sepals acuminate and the inflorescence more strictly terminal.
</paragraph>
